[b]Reversal Engine Score v1 [WavesUnchained][/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
Reversal Engine Score detects liquidity-sweep reversals: price violates a prior swing low/high and recovers by close on the same bar. A signal fires only when all mandatory gates pass on a confirmed bar and the optional quality score meets your per-direction minimum. This keeps the signal count low and evidence-backed.

[b]Mandatory gates (all required)[/b]
[list]
[*][b]Liquidity sweep[/b] — prior swing violated, recovery close on the same bar
[*][b]Close position[/b] — close in the upper (long) / lower (short) third of the bar range
[*][b]Body size[/b] — candle body above ATR × factor
[*][b]ATR corridor[/b] — volatility between configurable min/max vs. the ATR baseline; filters both noise phases and spike/news regimes
[*][b]HTF trend[/b] — dual-EMA filter on a configurable higher timeframe must not oppose the signal
[*][b]Spike filter[/b] — sweeps deeper than N×ATR are blocked (real breakdowns, not reversals)
[/list]

[b]Optional quality score (0–2)[/b]
[list]
[*][b]Long:[/b] RSI > 50 (+1), no lower-low structure (+1)
[*][b]Short:[/b] RSI > 50 — still elevated, reversal from overbought (+1), no higher-high structure (+1)
[*]Quality tiers A/B/C shown at the signal label; minimum quality configurable per direction
[/list]

[b]Risk levels[/b]
[list]
[*][b]SL:[/b] sweep low/high plus a configurable ATR noise buffer — structure is the primary stop
[*][b]TP:[/b] R-multiple of the actual risk distance (entry to structural SL)
[/list]

[b]Outputs[/b]
[list]
[*]BUY / SELL markers with quality tier and full gate breakdown in the tooltip
[*]Outcome tracking: the label turns blue when no follow-through occurs within the configured window
[*]Optional structure labels (HH / HL / LH / LL) at confirmed pivots
[*]SL and TP lines at the signal bar, HTF trend background (optional)
[*]Hidden plots for strategy use: entry, stop, take, direction, score
[*]Alert conditions for BUY, SELL, and either
[/list]

